Content:: Bezimenne (Ukrainian: Безіменне; Russian: Безыменное) is a village in Novoazovsk Raion (district) in Donetsk Oblast of eastern Ukraine, at 133 km SSE from the centre of Donetsk city, on the shore of the Sea of Azov. The settlement was taken under control of pro-Russian forces during the War in Donbass, which started in 2014.[1][2] Native language as of the Ukrainian Census of 2001:[3]  This article about a location in Donetsk Oblast is a stub.
